The paper proposes a deep learning method for non-Euclidean structured data such as graphs, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. The paper specifically focuses on graph convolutional architectures, which is a subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as they are also related to deep learning. Additionally, the paper mentions recommender systems, which falls under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and natural language processing, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
